title: Readonly
extract: read only - Computer Definition. (1) Refers to storage media that permanently hold their content such as ROM chips, CD-ROMs and DVD-ROMs. See ROM, CD-ROM and DVD-ROM. (2) A file that can be read, but not updated or erased. See file attribute.
